When organisers of the Comrades Marathon announced the return of the race for this year, it was like a weight off the shoulders of runners. eNCA's Siphokazi Malinga reports. #DStv403 DURBAN - Road runners now have a clear purpose in their training. After two years of uncertainty and frustration, 15,000 athletes can now get back into their preparation routine for the world’s biggest ultra-marathon. READ: Comrades celebrations continue despite no race The down run this year will start from Pietermaritzburg on 28 August, giving runners enough time to prepare for the gruelling 90 kilometres to Durban. * eNCA's Siphokazi Malinga reports.